	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Welp all i know is that if you run out of mana your entire party is good as dead.  My general rule of thumb is to have 60+ mana at all times for heals.  Adds can be nasty and deadly.  <BR>
<BR>
There are many times that we as clerics definitely need to use this spell.  I had a group once where the puller pulled 5.  I healed the tanks up once they were on mob 2 and finished it of quick so they could start killing 3.  Of course that then brought mob 4 and 5 to me and i expected this.  This is one of the main reasons i think we are able to wear plate.  We will take a beating.<BR>
<BR>
Clerics function to keep the group alive in whatever means it takes.  If that means throwing in a dd to speed up the fight...if it means rooting adds....if it means stunning a casting mob so it doesn't heal itself or other mobs...and mostly to heal the party and have mana to heal them.  This means doing your thing and sitting on your BUTT!!!  Standing and doing it again.  <BR>
<BR>
I will never understand how some of you think it is ok to melee...it isn't.  The time it takes to melee takes away from getting some of that mana back even just for one more heal in battle.  And getting back to the point here....wrath is a necessary part of keeping the party alive especially when there are a few mobs that party must take down all at once.<BR>
<BR>
26th cleric<BR>
Lanys
				</font>
			</td>

